<p>I have followed <a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ebs-expand-volume.html" rel="nofollow">AWS guide</a> to expand the 8GB volume to 16GB.</p>  <p>What I have done is:</p>  <ol> <li>Take snapshot of 8GB volume</li> <li>Create new 16GB volume by the snapshot</li> <li>Detach 8GB volume from EC2 instance, then attach 16GB volume to that EC2 instance</li> </ol>  <p>After that, <code>df -h</code>:</p>  <pre><code>Filesystem      Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on /dev/xvda1       16G   11G  5.3G  67% / </code></pre>  <p>Why the <code>Used</code> size increase to 11G? It should be 8G.</p>